u$ denotes the derivative with respect to the outer unit normal $
u$. We show that any positive very weak solution of this problem belongs to $L^\infty$ provided the functions $f,g,	ilde f,	ilde g$ satisfy suitable polynomial growth conditions. In addition, all positive solutions are uniformly bounded provided the right-hand sides are bounded in $L^1$. We also prove that our growth conditions are optimal. Finally, we show that our results remain true for problems involving nonlocal nonlinearities and we use our a priori estimates to prove the existence of positive solutions.
